data.value: This section allows management of banned IP addresses. Banned addresses can be added, edited and deleted here. Addresses can be banned globally or separately for particular sites.

data.name: Administration.Categories.Description
data.value: This section displays a hierarchy of categories defined for your websites. You can either create a new category, or edit or delete the existing ones. You can manage your personal categories as well.

data.name: Administration.CMS.Activities.Description
data.value: This section enables you to work with activities. You are able to view list of logged activities. You can also create new custom activities.

data.name: Administration.CMS.ContactManagement.Description
data.value: This section enables to work with Accounts and Contacts. You are able to assign Contacts to Accounts and vice versa. You can also split&merge Contacts and Accounts. You can create dynamic or static Contact groups or manage specific statuses.

data.value: This section displays an event log. You can select to display the log for the whole system or for one particular site. The log can also be cleared here. Detailed information about each of the logged events can also be displayed.

data.value: This section is used for setting site permissions. Permissions for individual user roles can be set here for particular modules and document types of given website.

data.name: Administration.Roles.Description
data.value: This section displays a list of user roles defined for your websites. You can either create new role, or edit or delete existing roles. You can display available roles for given site or assign users to given role.

data.name: Administration.ScheduledTasks.Description
data.value: This section displays a list of scheduled tasks and allows their management. You can either create new task, refresh the task list or edit, delete and execute existing tasks. For each task, you can specify the interval of execution. You can also execute the task manually and edit or delete it.

data.name: administration.ui.categoriesdescription

data.name: administration.ui.emailtemplatesdescription

data.name: Administration.UIPersonalization.Description

data.value: Name of the add to cart conversion used in web analytics.

data.name: documentation.webpart.addtocartconversionregistrationvalue
data.value: Sets a number that will be recorded along with the specified conversion when a product is added to the shopping cart. The values are cumulative, i.e. when a conversion hit is logged, the specified value will be added to the total sum previously recorded for this conversion. You may insert a macro expression into this field to dynamically retrieve a value from the current site context.

data.name: documentation.webpart.allowuserchangedisplayname
data.value: Indicates if administrators should be able to edit the group's display name.

data.name: documentation.webpart.conversionregistrationvalue
data.value: Sets a number that will be recorded along with the registration conversion when it is logged. The values are cumulative, i.e. when a conversion hit is logged, the specified value will be added to the total sum previously recorded for this conversion. You may insert a macro expression into this field to dynamically retrieve a value from the current site context.

data.name: documentation.webpart.loadpagesindividually
data.value: If checked, the data source loads and caches individual pages from the database instead of loading the complete data of all pages at once. This property is used only if paging is enabled. Using this setting also requires the "Order by" property to be set.

data.name: documentation.webpart.orderconversionvalue
data.value: Sets a number that will be recorded along with the Order conversion when it is logged. The values are cumulative, i.e. when a conversion hit is logged, the specified value will be added to the total sum previously recorded for this conversion. You may insert a macro expression into this field to dynamically retrieve a value from the current site context.

data.name: documentation.webpart.pm.mytasks.allowtaskaction
data.value: Indicates whether users with the appropriate permissions should be allowed to perform task actions (create or delete tasks).

data.name: documentation.webpart.pm.projecttasks.allowtaskaction
data.value: Indicates whether users with the appropriate permissions may delete tasks.

data.name: documentation.webpart.pm.sitename
data.value: Can be used to select if tasks should be displayed from all sites, or only the current site.

data.name: documentation.webpart.taskdetailurl
data.value: Contains the URL of a page that is linked when the displayed message is clicked. If left empty, the value is taken from the 'Site Manager -> Settings -> Intranet & Collaboration -> Projects -> Task detail page' field. If neither of these locations contain a value, the message will not work as a link.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.abusereportconfirm
data.value: Sets the confirmation text displayed after an abuse report is successfully submitted by a user.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.abusereporttitle
data.value: Sets the title used to identify the reports submitted by this web part in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Abuse report. This property can be used to distinguish reports from different sections of a website.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.acceleratorbuttontext
data.value: Sets the text caption of the button.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.acceleratordescription
data.value: Sets the descritpion of the search accelerator for the Internet Explorer context menu.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.acceleratorname
data.value: Sets the name of the search accelerator in the Internet Explorer context menu.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.allowdesignmode
data.value: If checked, actions that allow users to manage (add, remove or resize) the sections of the layout will be available directly in the design mode. If disabled, the layout will have to be managed through the property configuration dialog of the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.applymenudesign
data.value: Indicates if document settings for menu design should be applied to the navigation items displayed by the web part. These settings can be configured for individual documents in CMS Desk -> Content -> Edit -> Properties -> Menu.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.attachmentgroup
data.value: Allows the selection of the document field from which the attachments will be loaded. This field must use the 'Document attachments control' form control. If empty, attachments bound to the DocumentID field (managable via CMS Desk -> Properties -> Attachments) will be selected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.attachmentimagemaxsidesize
data.value: Sets the maximum side size of images displayed in forum post attachments.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.attachmentpath
data.value: Specifies the path of the document from which attachments will be loaded. If empty, the curent document will be used automatically.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.backnextlocation
data.value: Indicates if the buttons used for navigating to the previous and next page should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardbaseurl
data.value: URL used as the URL base of links to message boards in notification e-mails. If empty, value from Site Manager -> Settings -> Community -> Message boards -> Board base URL will be used. If that property is empty too, message boards can not be placed on pages with wildcard URLs.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.bodycssclass
data.value: Name of the CSS class which will be added to the BODY tag's class attribute. The specified class must be defined in the site's current CSS stylesheet for the styling to take effect.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.cachedependencies
data.value: Contains a list of cache keys on which the partial cache of the web part depends. When the specified cache items change, the partial cache of the web part is deleted. Each line may only contain a single item. If the Use default cache dependencies box is checked, the default dependencies will be used, which include all possible object changes that could affect the specific web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.calendardayfield
data.value: Sets the document field from which the web part will obtain the dates used to place items into the calendar. The field must use the 'Date and time' data type. If left empty, the 'DocumentModifiedWhen' column will be used by default (documents will be displayed in the calendar according to the date when they were last modified).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.calendartransformation
data.value: Sets the transformation used to display items in the calendar. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.combinewithdefaultculture
data.value: Indicates whether search results should be retrieved from documents in the default culture in addition to the culture that is currently selected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.containercssclass
data.value: CSS class used for the container. Applied only if the {%ContainerCSSClass%} macro is used as the value of the Class attribute in the code of the container.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.containercustomcontent
data.value: Custom content to be used in the container. Applied only if the {%ContainerCustomContent%} macro is used in the code of the container.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.containerhideonsub
data.value: Indicates if the web part container should be hidden on sub-pages.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.conversionname
data.value: Selects the conversion object used to track the actions that users perform via the web part/widget.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.conversionvalue
data.value: Sets a number that will be recorded along with the conversion when the tracked action is performed. The values are cumulative, i.e. when a conversion hit is logged, the specified value will be added to the total sum previously recorded for this conversion. You may insert a macro expression into this field to dynamically retrieve a value from the current site context.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.cssfiles
data.value: Can be used to specify the path to external stylesheet files that are required to generate the effect. A request for these stylesheets will be added to the head element of the page. Each path must be entered on a new line. For example: ~/CMSWebParts/Viewers/Effects/lightbox_files/lightbox.css

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.culture
data.value: Sets the culture code of the documents that should be included in searches. If empty, the current culture is searched. The ##ALL## macro can be used to search in documents of all cultures.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.customtable
data.value: Allows the selection of the custom table from which data should be loaded.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.datasourcecheckperm
data.value: Indicates if permissions should be checked for the displayed content and only the items for which the current user has appropriate permission should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.datasourcenamedocuments
data.value: In order to display documents provided by a data source web part, its Web part control ID must be entered into this property. The data source web part must be placed on the same page. Only the Documents data source may be connected to this web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.defaulttargeturl
data.value: Specifies the URL of the page where users should be redirected after they successfully log in. For example: ~/clientportal.aspx. This property is ignored if a different URL is passed through the ReturnUrl query string parameter (e.g. when a user is redirected to a logon page after they attempt to access a website section that requires authentication).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.directpage
data.value: Sets the transformation that implements direct page changing. Use a text box or drop-down list control with an ID set to "directPageControl" to register the page change event.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.disablemacros
data.value: If checked, macros contained in the values of the web part's properties will no longer be resolved.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.disableonsub
data.value: Indicates if the web part should be disabled on sub-pages. If checked, the web part will not perform its function on child documents that inherit the page template containing the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displayattachmentimage
data.value: Determines whether images in forum post attachments should be displayed directly in the post. If not checked, only links to the images will be shown.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaybadgeinfo
data.value: Indicates whether badge information should be displayed for post authors in the forums.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displayblogpostssubscriptions
data.value: Indicates if subscriptions to blog posts should be displayed to users on the Subscriptions tab.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displayhighlighteditemaslink
data.value: Indicates if items in the menu that are part of the currently selected path should be displayed as links.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaymessageboardssubscriptions
data.value: Indicates if subscriptions to message boards should be displayed to users on the Subscriptions tab.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaynewsletterssubscriptions
data.value: Indicates if newsletter subscriptions should be displayed to users on the Subscriptions tab.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.docperpage
data.value: Sets the default number of items that will be displayed at the same time. If the amount of items exceeds the selected number, the remaining items will be accessible using the pager.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.documentage
data.value: Filters documents according to their age in days. Only documents that are older than the first value and newer than the second will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.documentname
data.value: Filters documents according to their document name. Only documents that contain the entered string somewhere in their name will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.documentsorderby
data.value: Selects the data field according to which the displayed items will be sorted by default.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enabled
data.value: Indicates if the web part is enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enablepostspaging
data.value: Indicates if the posts in a thread should be paged. Paging can only be applied if the selected Forum layout supports paging (Flat).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enableuserafterregistration
data.value: Indicates if users should automatically be enabled after registration. Please note that if the website is configured to require e-mail confirmation or administrator approval for registration, users will always be disabled when they register.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.encodemenucaption
data.value: Indicates whether HTML encoding should be applied to the navigation items. Useful only in special cases where the names of the displayed documents contain HTML code.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.failuretext
data.value: Sets the text displayed to users if authentication fails. For example: Incorrect user name or password.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.firsttransform
data.value: Sets the transformation applied to the first item displayed on every hierarchical level. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.forumsenableavatars
data.value: Indicates if user avatar images should be displayed in the forums.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.friendlybaseurl
data.value: Sets the path that will serve as the base of the friendly URLs used by the forums, e.g. /Forums. If empty, the URL of the current document is used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.friendlyurlextension
data.value: Sets the extension that should be used in the friendly URLs. For extensionless URLs, leave the property blank.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.generateurlswithlangprefix
data.value: Indicates if the URLs of the links should be generated with a language prefix. This property is usable only if language prefixes for URLs are enabled for the website, which can be done in Site Manager -> Settings -> URLs and SEO.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridallowsorting
data.value: Indicates if sorting according to individual columns should be allowed in the displayed grid.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridcolumnselector
data.value: Allows the selection and configuration of the columns that should be displayed in the grid. Please be aware that it is impossible to display columns that are not loaded by the web part (depending on the settings of the 'Selected columns' property). The selection dialog provides the option to display the values of a column as links. If you wish to use this function, your query must retrieve the NodeAliasPath and DocumentUrlPath columns (e.g. from the View_CMS_Tree_Joined view), so that an appropriate URL can be generated for the links.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridpagingmode
data.value: Allows the selection of the method used for navigation between pages. The options are Previous/Next buttons and page number links.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridsetfirstpageaftersortchange
data.value: Indicates if the first page should be displayed instead of the current page after the sorting of the grid is changed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridshowfooter
data.value: Indicates if the grid footer should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridshowheader
data.value: Indicates if the grid header should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridsortascending
data.value: Indicates if the default sorting order should be ascending.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridsortfield
data.value: Sets the name of the field used to sort the records in the grid by default.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.gridtooltip
data.value: Sets the tooltip displayed when a user hovers their mouse over the grid.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.groupsize
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of page number links that will be displayed together. Any additional links that do not fit can be accessed in the next or previous group.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hideheadfootforsingle
data.value: If checked, the header and footer transformations will not be applied if only a single item is displayed on a given hierarchical level.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hidelayoutforzerorows
data.value: Indicates if the content specified using the Content before/after properties in the Layout category should be hidden if no items to be displayed are retrieved.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hidepagerforsinglepage
data.value: Indicates whether the pager should be hidden if the displayed items fit onto a single page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hideunavaliblecultures
data.value: Indicates whether links for cultures that are not available for the current document should be hidden.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hierarchdisplaymode
data.value: Allows the hierarchical display mode to be selected. Inner: generates sub-levels inside the parent item (tree structure). Separate: generates sub-levels outside of the items on parent levels (flat structure).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hierarchfootertransform
data.value: Sets the transformation used at the end of every hierarchical level. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hierarchheadertransform
data.value: Sets the transformation used at the beginning of every hierarchical level. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hierarchicaltransformation
data.value: Sets the transformation to be used for the displayed documents in list view mode. This property can be used to set both standard and hierarchical transformations. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.highlightallitemsinpath
data.value: If enabled, all items on the path of the currently selected document will also be selected (highlighted) in the menu.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.highlightednodepath
data.value: Sets the path of the document that should be selected in the menu by default. If empty, the path of the currently selected document is used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.idcolumnname
data.value: Sets the name of the column which serves as a unique identifier for objects. It is used in a parent-child relationship with the column specified in the 'ParentID column' property. It is recommended to use the NodeID column when displaying documents.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.inclfinishedtasks
data.value: If enabled, tasks that have a status designating them as finished will be counted by the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.inclnotstartedtasks
data.value: If enabled, tasks that have a status designating them as not yet started will be counted by the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.includejquery
data.value: If enabled, the jQuery core script will automatically be included on the page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.indexes
data.value: Allows the selection of one or more smart search indexes that should be used for searching.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.initscript
data.value: Contains the script that initializes the effect applied to the displayed items.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.inlinecss
data.value: Can be used to specify additional inline CSS styles that will be placed directly into the page header.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.itemhtmlafter
data.value: HTML content placed after each of the generated items. This content is not used if a single selected document is viewed in detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.itemhtmlbefore
data.value: HTML content placed before each of the generated items. This content is not used if a single selected item is viewed in detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lasttransform
data.value: Sets the transformation applied to the last item displayed on every hierarchical level. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.levelcolumnname
data.value: Sets the name of the column used to determine an object's level in the hierarchy. It is recommended to use the NodeLevel column when displaying documents.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxanimate
data.value: Indicates if the lightbox animation should be enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxbordersize
data.value: Sets the width of the image border in the lightbox.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxgroup
data.value: Sets a group name for the generated lightbox. It is necessary to set this property when displaying multiple lightboxes on a single page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxheight
data.value: Sets the height of the frame used in lightbox detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxloaddelay
data.value: Sets the load delay time (in miliseconds). When using automatic resizing, this value indicates how long the lightbox will take to reach the size of the displayed element. If there are problems displaying lightbox content, try to use a higher value.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxoverlayopacity
data.value: Determines the transparency of the lightbox background. Must be a decimal number between 0 and 1, where 0 is fully transparent and 1 is completely dark.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxpermanentnavigation
data.value: If checked, the navigations buttons will always be visible in lightbox detail view mode. Otherwise they will only be shown on mouse over.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxresizespeed
data.value: Allows the selection of the image resizing speed. Options range from 1 (slowest) to 10 (fastest).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lightboxwidth
data.value: Sets the width of the frame used in lightbox detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.linkselectedtext
data.value: Sets the text displayed for the given link if it is currently selected by the user. You can insert HTML code into this field.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.linktitle
data.value: Sets the title (tooltip) for the link used to select the given style option.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.listingtype
data.value: Selects which category of documents should be displayed. If the All option is chosen, some documents may be listed multiple times if they fit the conditions of more than one category.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.loadhierarchdata
data.value: Indicates whether documents should be loaded with regard to their hierarchical position in the content tree. Hierarchical data has a parent-child relationship (NodeID/NodeParentID). Hierarchical transformations can be used for this type of data. Please be aware that hierarchical data cannot be displayed if paging is enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.logonpageurl
data.value: Sets the URL of the logon page to which unauthorized users are redirected if the "Redirect unauthorized users" property is enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.maxpages
data.value: Sets the maximum number of pages which should be displayed, even if the results are divided into more pages.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.maxrelativelevel
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of allowed levels in the forum post hierarchy. For example, setting 1 would only let users reply to the first post of each thread. Entering -1 causes the level to be unlimited.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.medialibraryname
data.value: Content of this media library will be displayed by the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.messageboard
data.value: Selects the specific message board (or all boards) from which the posts will be loaded.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.navcolumns
data.value: Lists database columns that should be loaded in addition to the set used by default; separated by commas (,). Entering an asterisk (*) causes all columns to be loaded. It is recommended to load only those columns that are necessary.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.navigationdocumenttypes
data.value: Determines which document types should be displayed, specified by a list of code names separated by semicolons (;). By default, only CMS.MenuItem documents (pages) are displayed in navigation.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.navigationpath
data.value: Specifies the path of the documents that should be displayed. If empty, the path will be set to all documents of the given website (/%).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.navigationtreeorderby
data.value: Sets the value of the ORDER BY clause in the SELECT statement used to retrieve the content. Please be aware that it is necessary for the root of the displayed tree (or sub-tree) to be first in the resulting order, otherwise all documents may not be displayed correctly. This can be ensured by having the value of this property start with the NodeLevel column, such as for example: NodeLevel, NodeOrder

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.noeventtransf
data.value: Sets the transformation used for days without any items to be displayed. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.noresultstext
data.value: Sets the text that is displayed if no search results are found.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagenumbersseparator
data.value: Contains the HTML code of a separator to be placed between the page number links.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagerhtmlafter
data.value: Contains the HTML code placed on the page after the pager.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagerhtmlbefore
data.value: Contains the HTML code placed on the page before the pager.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.parentidcolumnname
data.value: Sets the name of the column that contains the unique identifier of an object's parent. It is used in a parent-child relationship with the column specified in the 'ID column' property. It is recommended to use the NodeParentID column when displaying documents.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.partialcacheminutes
data.value: Sets the number of minutes for which the output HTML code of the web part should remain cached. This process is similar to full-page caching, but only for the code of the web part specifically. If left empty or set to 0, partial caching will be not be used for the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pm.allowcreatefor
data.value: Designates what type of users can manage the displayed projects (create/modify projects and tasks). The selection made in this property overrides the security settings of individual projects.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pm.authorizedroles
data.value: Sets the roles that should be authorized to manage the displayed projects. This option is used only if the Authorized roles option is selected in the 'Project can be managed by' property.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.postspagesize
data.value: Sets the number of posts displayed per page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.project
data.value: Allows the selection of the projects whose tasks should be displayed. All projects from the current site that do not belong under any group are available.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.querycolumns
data.value: Lists the columns (separated by commas) that should be loaded by the specified query. For this property to be applied, the used query must contain the ##COLUMNS## macro expression after its SELECT statement.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.queryorderby
data.value: Sets the value of the ORDER BY clause in the query used to retrieve data. For this property to be applied, the used query must have the ##ORDERBY## macro expression as the value of its ORDER BY clause.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.queryselecttopn
data.value: Sets the maximum amount of items to be retrieved by the specified query. For this property to be applied, the used query must contain the ##TOPN## macro expression directly after its SELECT statement.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.querywhere
data.value: Sets the value of the WHERE clause in the query used to retrieve data. For this property to be applied, the used query must have the ##WHERE## macro expression as the value of its WHERE clause.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.redirecttouserprofile
data.value: Indicates whether the usernames of forum post authors should serve as links to the given user's profile page. This requires the Site Manager -> Settings -> Community -> Member profile path setting to be configured properly.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.registrationapprovalpage
data.value: Sets the URL of the page where users can confirm their registration. This page will be linked in the registration confirmation e-mail. The page must contain the Registration e-mail confirmation web part to work correctly.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.registrationassigntoroles
data.value: Can be used to set a list of roles to which users will be assigned when they register through the web part. The roles must be specified using their code names and separated by semicolons (;). For example: CMSPublicUsers;CMSEditors

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.registrationassigntosites
data.value: Can be used to select which sites users should automatically be assigned to when they register through the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.renderimagealt
data.value: Indicates if ALT attributes should be rendered for all images used in the menu (for XHTML compatibility).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.renderlinktitle
data.value: If enabled, the menu will render document names as Title attributes (tooltips) for all links. This can improve the accessibility of your website.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.repeatcolumns
data.value: Sets the number of columns into which the displayed items will be divided.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.repeatdirection
data.value: Determines the direction in which items should be displayed when multiple columns are used - can be either vertical or horizontal.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.repeaterhtmlafter
data.value: HTML content placed after the list of generated items. This can be used to define the layout required for the effect, e.g. by adding closing block elements. The content is not used if a single selected document is viewed in detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.repeaterhtmlbefore
data.value: HTML content placed before the list of generated items. This property can be used to define the layout required for the desired effect, e.g. by adding wrapping block elements to apply CSS classes. The content is not used if a single selected document is viewed in detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.repeatlayout
data.value: Allows the selection of the layout that should be used when displaying items. The available options are table or flow (no predefined structure).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.reportchart
data.value: Selects the report and specific chart that will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.resultsposition
data.value: Allows the position of the paging results summary text to be selected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.rssitemscount
data.value: Number of items to be displayed in the RSS feed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.scriptfiles
data.value: Can be used to specify the path to external script files that are required to generate the effect. A request for these scripts will be added to the head element of the page. Each path must be entered on a new line. For example: ~/CMSWebParts/Viewers/Effects/lightbox_files/jquery.js

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchbutton
data.value: Sets the text caption of the search button.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchCheckPermissions
data.value: Indicates whether the web part should filter out documents for which the current user does not have the "read" permission from search results.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchcondition
data.value: Sets a search condition that is added to any conditions specified in the search expression. You can use special characters (+ -) and field conditions (e.g. +documentnodeid:(int)255).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchdocumentTypes
data.value: Allows document searches to be restricted to specific document types. Document types must be entered using their code names and separated by semicolons (;). If empty, all document types specified by the index are searched.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchforlabel
data.value: Sets the text displayed before the search textbox.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchmaxresults
data.value: Sets the maximum number of search results that can be displayed. If empty, no limits are used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchmode
data.value: Sets the default search mode. The options are searching for results that contain all words in the entered expression, any of the words or only the exact phrase.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchmodelabel
data.value: Sets the text displayed before the search mode selector.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchOptions
data.value: Sets the level of syntax that is allowed in search expressions: Basic - users are allowed to input special syntax, but cannot search specific fields(field:value). None - users can only enter text, everything is processed as a part of the search expression. Full - all search options can be used, including field searching.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchorderby
data.value: Sets the ORDER BY expression that defines the order in which document attachments will be displayed in search results.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchpath
data.value: Can be used to limit the path that is searched by document searches.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchresultspageurl
data.value: URL of the page where the search results are displayed. This page must contain either the Smart search results or Smart search dialog with results web part. If empty, the current page is used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchsort
data.value:
Defines the order in which search results are displayed. You can specify one or more document fields (separated by commas) according to which the results will be sorted. The ##SCORE## macro can be used to order results by their score (relevance). The default order is ascending, you can change this using the DESC keyword (e.g. articleid DESC).
If you encounter the "field <fieldname> does not appear to be indexed" error when using multiple indexes, try specifying the type of the field using the following syntax: (date)createdwhen

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.searchwhere
data.value: Sets the WHERE condition that limits which documents should have their attachments searched.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecteddatabasecolumnname
data.value: Sets which custom table field should be used to identify records for selection. This field must be a unique identifier.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectedfootertransf
data.value: Sets the transformation placed after an item when it is displayed in detail view mode. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectedheadertransf
data.value: Sets the transformation placed before an item when it is displayed in detail view mode. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecteditemcolumn
data.value: Sets the name of the column which should be used to identify the currently selected item. It is recommended to use the DocumentID column when displaying documents.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecteditemvalue
data.value: Can be used to enter a value of the column specified in the 'Selected item value' property to designate the currently selected item. The {%currentpageinfo.documentid%} macro can be entered to dynamically give the value of the current document.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectedquerystringkeyname
data.value: Sets the name of the URL query string parameter used to determine which custom table record should be selected for detail view mode.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectedvalidationtype
data.value: Allows the selection of the type of validation that should be applied to the input of the query string parameter that determines custom table record selection.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecttopndocuments
data.value: Specifies the maximum amount of documents to be loaded. If empty, all possible documents will be selected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sendconfirmationemails
data.value: If true, confirmation e-mails will be sent to users who subscribe or unsubscribe to/from a newsletter.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sendwelcomeemail
data.value: Indicates whether a welcome e-mail should be sent to users after registration. The e-mails are based on the appropriate e-mail template (depends if the website is configured to require e-mail confirmation or administrator approval for registration).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showcurrentitemaslink
data.value: Indicates whether the current breadcrumbs item should be generated as a link.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showfinishedprojects
data.value: If enabled, projects that have a status designating them as finished will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showfinishedtasks
data.value: If enabled, tasks that have a status designating them as finished will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showglobaleventsonly
data.value: Indicates if only events that are not related to a specific site should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showontime
data.value: If enabled, tasks that haven't yet reached their deadline will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showoverdue
data.value: If enabled, tasks that have passed their deadline will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showprivate
data.value: If enabled, private tasks will be displayed. Private tasks are visible only by users who are involved in them.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showsearchmode
data.value: Indicates if the search mode selector should be displayed to users.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showsignout
data.value: If enabled, the web part will display a sign out link for authenticated users.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showstatusas
data.value: Selects the way that task statuses should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.signinimageurl
data.value: Specifies the URL of an image that will be used for the sign in button if the Sign in text property is empty.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.signoutimageurl
data.value: Specifies the URL of an image that will be used for the sign out button if the Sign out text property is empty.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.singletransform
data.value: Sets the transformation applied when only a single item is displayed on a hierarchical level. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.site
data.value: Allows the selection of the site from which content should be loaded. Global administrators have the option of selecting all sites.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.skinid
data.value: Sets the SkinID of the skin that should be applied to the web part. The skin must be defined in the Default.skin file located in the App_Themes directory under the folder of the stylesheet used by the page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sorting
data.value: Determines whether the default sorting order should be ascending or descending.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spfields
data.value: If the Use dataset property is enabled, this field can be used to specify which of the retrieved fields should be converted to columns in the dataset (field names must be separated by semicolons). If empty, all fields will be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spitemidfield
data.value: If entered, items will be selected based on the presence of this key in the URL query string.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spitemidfieldtype
data.value: Used to specify the type of the itemID field. The two basic types are Text (for string values) and Counter (for IDs). More information can be found at http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms437580.aspx

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.splistname
data.value: Name of the SharePoint list(or picture library) from which the list items/pictures should be loaded. This field is case sensitive!

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spquery
data.value: Can be used to set a query to filter which rows should be loaded or change their order. It uses CAML syntax. A sample query could look like the following: <Query><Where><Eq><FieldRef Name="ID" /><Value Type="Counter">1</Value></Eq></Where></Query> More information can be found at http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dd586530.aspx

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sprowlimit
data.value: Sets the maximum number of items (data rows) to be retrieved.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spselecteditemfieldname
data.value: Determines which field is used for item selection. Original field names are used here - without the ows_ prefix. This property is case sensitive!

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spservicemode
data.value: Determines what kind of data will be loaded by the web part. This also automatically sets the appropriate web service to be used. The selected mode may affect the behaviour of some of the web part's other properties.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spservicepassword
data.value: Sets the password used for authentication against the web service. If empty, the credentials specified in Site Manager -> Settings -> Integration -> Microsoft SharePoint will be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spserviceurl
data.value: Specifies the URL of the SharePoint site that should be used or the direct URL of the requested web service (Eg. Lists.asmx, Imaging.asmx). If only the site URL is entered, then the web service used for data retrieval is automatically determined according to the value of the Mode property.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spserviceusername
data.value: Sets the username for authentication against the web service. If empty, the credentials specified in Site Manager -> Settings -> Integration -> Microsoft SharePoint will be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spshowreturnedcaml
data.value: If enabled, the retrieved data will be displayed in raw CAML format. This can be useful for debugging purposes or when searching for the content of specific fields.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sptransformationname
data.value: Sets the transformation used to display the listed data. Standard ASCX transformations should be selected if the Use dataset property is enabled, otherwise XSLT can be used to transform CAML directly to HTML. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spuseclassicdataset
data.value: If enabled, the retrieved XML data will be converted to a dataset that can be used with standard ASCX transformations. If disabled, the data will not be modified and can be converted to HTML using XSLT.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.spviewfields
data.value: Directly specifies the names of the SharePoint list fields that should be loaded. If empty all fields will be retrieved. Note: Certain fields will always be retrieved.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sqlsearch
data.value: Indicates if the content of document attachments should be included in searches. The SQL server must be properly configured for full-text search before attachment searching is possible.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.tagcloud.selectpublished
data.value: Indicates if only tags from published documents should be displayed. Applied only when 'Site name' or 'Alias path' property is defined. If not, all tags from the selected tag group will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.taskinfotext
data.value: Sets the text of the displayed message. It may contain the {0} formatting macro expression, which will be resolved into the number of tasks assigned to the current user.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.threadpagesize
data.value: Sets the number of threads displayed per page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.threadviewmode
data.value: Sets the default mode used to display forum posts under threads. Only applied if the Forum layout property is set to flat.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.transformationfeed
data.value: Transformation used for generating the feed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.transformationname
data.value: Sets the transformation according to which the search results will be displayed. Predefined result transformations can be found under the CMS.Root document type.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.urltarget
data.value: Specifies the name of the target frame in which the navigation links will be opened. For example: _blank

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.usefordocumenttypes
data.value: Contains a list of document types on which the web part should be used. If the currently selected document uses the page template containing the web part, but its type is not specified by this property, the web part will not be functional. The document types in the list must be specified by their code names and separated by semicolons (;). If empty, the web part will be enabled on all document types.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.useforroles
data.value: The web part will only perform its function if the current user is assigned to one of the roles specified in this list. This may be used to implement documents with specific functionality for different types of users. The roles in the list must be specified by their code names and separated by semicolons (;). If empty, the web part will work for all users.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.usehiearechorder
data.value: Indicates whether the default hierarchical order should be used when displaying documents. This order is applied only if the LoadHierarchicalData property is enabled. The default order value is "NodeLevel, NodeOrder". The value of the ORDER BY expression property is added to the end of the order by clause.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.webparttitle
data.value: Title of the web part displayed on the Design tab of CMS Desk. If empty, the value of the Web part control ID property is used for this purpose.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.wordwrap
data.value: Indicates if long menu item captions should be broken into multiple lines (word wrapped).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.zonetitle
data.value: Title of the zone displayed on the Design tab.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.zonetype
data.value: The following zone types are available: None - a standard web part zone is used. User personalization - the zone will be set to contain widgets and website users will be able to personalize it on the live site. Customization by page editor - the zone will be set to contain widgets and website editors will be able to customize it on the Page tab of CMS Desk. Customization by group administrator - the zone will be set to contain widgets and group administrators of the group that owns the page will be able to customize it on the live site. Dashboard - this type of zone is only available on Dashboard page type templates. If selected, the zone will be set to contain widgets and users will be able to customize it on dashboard sections located in the CMS administration interface.

data.name: documentation.webparts.abuse.status
data.value: Allows the selection of a status according to which the displayed abuse reports will be filtered. Reports with a different status than chosen here will not be shown.

data.name: documentation.webparts.blogs.blogname
data.value: Selects the specific blog (or all blogs ) from which the comments will be loaded.

data.name: documentation.webparts.blogs.isapproved
data.value: Can be used to filter the listed comments according to their approval status (e.g. if the no option is selected, only comments that require approval will be displayed).

data.name: documentation.webparts.blogs.isspam
data.value: Can be used to filter the listed comments according to their spam flag.

data.name: documentation.webparts.forum.groups
data.value: Selects the forum groups from which posts should be displayed. If empty, all forum posts will be loaded, including those from ad-hoc forums.

data.name: documentation.widgetproperties.container
data.value: Selects which container (if any) should be displayed around the widget.

data.name: documentation.widgetproperties.containercssclass
data.value: CSS class used for the widget container. Applied only if the {%ContainerCSSClass%} macro is used as a value of the Class attribute of a wrapping element in container code.

data.name: documentation.widgetproperties.containercustomcontent
data.value: Custom content of the widget container. Applied only if the {%ContainerCustomContent%} macro is used in container code.

data.name: documentation.widgetproperties.containertitle
data.value: Sets the text of the title displayed in the header of the widget's container.

data.name: documentation.widgets.widgetpropertiestitle
data.value: Allows user to set widget title. If empty widget name is used.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.container
data.value: Specifies the name of the container (box) to be displayed around the entire web part zone. Only the containers defined at Site Manager -> Development -> Web part containers can be selected. The selected container can be edited directly by using the Edit button.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.containercssclass
data.value: CSS class used for the web part zone's container. Applied only if the {%ContainerCSSClass%} macro is used as the value of the Class attribute in the code of the container.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.containercustomcontent
data.value: Custom content to be displayed in the web part zone's container. Applied only if the code of the used container contains the {%ContainerCustomContent%} macro.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.containerhideonsub
data.value: Indicates if the web part zone container will be hidden on sub-pages.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.containertitle
data.value: Sets a title for the container (if one is specified for the web part zone). This title is displayed only if the {%ContainerTitle%} macro is used in the code of the container.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.contentafter
data.value: HTML content placed after the web part zone. Can be used to display a footer or close the tags contained in the 'ContentBefore' property, such as or elements.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.contentbefore
data.value: HTML content placed before the web part zone. Can be used to display a header or add some encapsulating code, such as <div> or <table> elements to achieve the required layout.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.displaytoroles
data.value: Contains a list of roles to which the web part zone should be displayed. This may be used to implement documents with specific functionality for different types of users. The roles in the list must be specified by their code names and separated by semicolons (;). If empty, the zone will be displayed to all users.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.hideonsub
data.value: Indicates if the web part zone will be hidden on sub-pages. If you check this box, the web part zone will be displayed only on the page that uses the page template with this web part zone and it will be hidden on all sub-pages that inherit the zone from a parent document.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.showfordocumenttypes
data.value: Indicates for which document types should the web part zone be displayed. If the type of the currently selected document is different, the web part zone is not displayed.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.visible
data.value: Indicates if the entire content of the web part zone should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.zoneproperties.zonetitle
data.value: Specifies the title of the web part zone. If not entered, code name of the web part zone is used.

data.name: documentlibrary.libraryrootnotexist
data.value: Document with specified library path ('{0}') does not exist.

data.name: documents.selectdocuments
data.value: You have to select some documents first.

data.name: DocumentType.FieldIsInherited
data.value: This item is inherited from document type '{0}', you need to edit it in that document type properties.

data.name: DocumentType_Edit_Transformation_Edit.UniqueTransformationNameCustomTable
data.value: Transformation with the same name already exists in this custom table.

data.name: DocumentType_New_Step7.Description
data.value: Please set search fields for Smart search module.

data.value: Document smart search specification was created.

data.name: ecommerce.customer.invalidemail
data.value: Customer does not have a valid e-mail address.

data.name: ecommerce.disablemaincurrencyerror
data.value: Currency "{0}" can't be disabled because it is set as main currency.

data.name: edit_user.membershipInfo
data.value: The user is assigned to the following memberships

data.name: EditCode.NotAllowed
data.value: You are not authorized to edit the ASCX code, you need to switch to HTML code type or contact the administrator to grant you with the required permissions.

data.name: EditCode.NotAllowedNoHtml
data.value: You are not authorized to edit the ASCX code, you need to contact the administrator to grant you with the required permissions.

data.name: EditContent.DocumentCannotCheckIn
data.value: The node has not been checked out, it cannot be checked in.

data.name: EditContent.DocumentCannotCheckOut
data.value: The node has already been checked out or is exclusively checked out by another user.

data.name: EditContent.DocumentCannotUndoCheckOut
data.value: There's no previous version to roll back.

data.name: editeddocument.notexists
data.value: The document you edited no longer exists, it was deleted by somebody else.

data.name: editedobject.notexists
data.value: The object you edited no longer exists, it was deleted by somebody else.

data.name: EditLayout.HintHtml
data.value: Use the following expression to add a new web part zone: {^WebPartZone|(id)zoneTopRight^} (ID must be unique)

data.name: editnewsletters.differentsite
data.value: Requested newsletter is not placed on the current site.

data.name: editnewsletters.differentsitesubscriber

By enabling this option, the "Version scheduled to be published" icon is enabled as well.

data.name: settingskey.cmsglobalcontactmultiplesites

data.name: settingskey.cmsgooglesitemapurl.description

data.name: settingskey.cmsgroupavatarmaxsidesize.description
data.value: Specifies maximal width or height of group avatar.

data.name: settingskey.cmsgroupmanagementpath.description
data.value: Alias path of group management page, e.g. "/Groups/{GroupName}/Management", where {GroupName} will be replaced by current group name.

data.name: settingskey.cmsgroupprofilepath.description
data.value: Alias path of group profile page, e.g. "/Groups/{GroupName}", where {GroupName} will be replaced by current group name.

data.name: settingskey.cmsgroupssecurityaccesspath.description
data.value: Alias path where user will be redirected when accessing group without appropriate permission, e.g. "/Groups/{GroupName}/Access", where {GroupName} will be replaced by current group name.

data.name: settingskey.cmsgrouptemplatepath.description
data.value: Alias path of a page which will be used as a template for new group.

data.name: settingskey.cmshideunavailableuserinterface.description
data.value: Indicates whether the user interface for unavailable modules should be shown

data.name: settingskey.cmsimagewatermark.description
data.value: Image name or path that will be used for watermarking the images. User either a full path (~/..) or just a file name from the ~/App_Themes/Default/Images/Watermarks folder.

data.name: settingskey.cmsimagewatermarkposition.description
data.value: The position where the image watermark is placed on the watermarked images.

data.name: settingskey.cmsindentoutputhtml.description
data.value: If checked, the output HTML of the pages is processed to produce nice, properly indented code. The setting is applied to all pages on which the XHTML output filter is enabled.

data.name: settingskey.CMSIntegrationEnabled.description
data.value: Indicates if the Integration bus logs and processes both incoming and outgoing integration tasks. Logging and processing of incoming and outgoing tasks can be enabled or disabled separately by means of the Enable logging of incoming tasks, Enable processing of incoming tasks, Enable logging of outgoing tasks and Enable processing of outgoing tasks settings below.

data.name: settingskey.CMSIntegrationLogExternal.description
data.value: Indicates if the Integration bus logs incoming integration tasks received from external systems. For this to work, the Enable system integration bus setting above must be enabled as well.

data.name: settingskey.CMSIntegrationLogInternal.description
data.value: Indicates if the Integration bus logs document and object changes made in the Kentico CMS system as outgoing integration tasks. For this to work, the Enable system integration bus setting above must be enabled as well.

data.name: settingskey.CMSIntegrationProcessExternal.description
data.value: Indicates if the Integration bus processes logged incoming integration tasks received from external systems. For this to work, the Enable system integration bus setting above must be enabled as well.

data.name: settingskey.CMSIntegrationProcessInternal.description
data.value: Indicates if the Integration bus processes outgoing integration tasks logged by document and object changes made in the Kentico CMS system. For this to work, the Enable system integration bus setting above must be enabled as well.

data.name: settingskey.cmsinvitationacceptationpath.description
data.value: Alias path of page containing webpart which is able to accept invitation.

data.name: settingskey.cmsinvitationvalidity.description
data.value: Number of days after which an invitation expires. Use 0 if it never expires.

data.name: settingskey.cmskeepchangeddocumentaccesible
data.value: Remember original URLs when moving documents

data.name: settingskey.cmskeepchangeddocumentaccesible.description
data.value: Specifies if new document alias should be created if document URL or alias path is updated or document is moved.

data.name: settingskey.cmslinkedinapikey.description
data.value: Identificator of your application, which you get when registering application at LinkedIn site.

data.name: settingskey.cmslinkedinapplicationsecret.description
data.value: This secret code will be used to encrypt all information between your site and LinkedIn servers.

data.name: settingskey.cmslinkedinroles.description
data.value: Registered LinkedIn users will be assigned to these roles. Separated by semicolon (;)

data.name: settingskey.cmsliveidconversionname.description
data.value: Default conversion name used for tracking registered users.

data.name: settingskey.cmsliveidrequireduserdatapage.description
data.value: URL of the page, where the RequiredLiveIDUsersData webpart is placed. If set, LiveID users are not directly created in the system and they must provide additional information on specified page.

data.name: settingskey.cmsliveidroles.description
data.value: Registred Windows Live users will be assigned to these roles. Separated by (;)

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogAnalytics.description
data.value: If enabled, web analytics debug log is saved into the loganalytics.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require web analytics debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogCache.description
data.value: If enabled, cache access debug log is saved into the logcache.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require cache access debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogEverythingToFile.description
data.value: Enables logging of all possible operations (including the Event log and E-mail sending log) into .log files stored in the ~/App_Data/ folder.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogFiles.description
data.value: If enabled, IO operation debug log is saved into the logfiles.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require IO operation debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogMacros.description
data.value: If enabled, macro debug log is saved into the logmacros.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require macro debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.cmslogmetadata.description
data.value: If enabled, changes of object and document metadata (i.e. when an object or document is created, edited or deleted) are logged in the Event log.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogOutputToFile.description
data.value: If enabled, output debug log is saved into the logOutput.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require output debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.cmslogpagenotfoundexception.description
data.value: If enabled, page not found (404) exceptions will be logged as a warning in the event log.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogRequests.description
data.value: If enabled, request debug log is saved into the logRequests.log and logRequestsUrls.log files in the ~\App_Data folder. The first file contains the full log, while the second one only lists requested URLs. This option does not require request debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogSecurity.description
data.value: If enabled, security debug log is saved into the logSecurity.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require security debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.cmslogsize.description
data.value: Number of events stored in the Event log. When exceeded by 10% (or a different percentage set by means of the CMSLogKeepPercent web.config key), the percentage of the oldest events is deleted from the log in a batch. If 0, no events are logged.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogSQLQueries.description
data.value: If enabled, SQL query debug log is saved into the logsql.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require SQL query debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogWebFarm
data.value: Log web farm operations to file

data.name: settingskey.CMSLogWebFarm.description
data.value: If enabled, web farm debug log is saved into the logwebfarm.log file in the ~\App_Data folder. This option does not require web farm debugging to be enabled.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmaxcachefilesize.description
data.value: Specifies the maximum size of the file in kilobytes that is allowed to be cached.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmaxtreenodes.description
data.value: Maximum number of documents that will be displayed under unfolded document in the tree view.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmaxuitreenodes.description
data.value: Maximum number of nodes displayed under one parent node in administration UI trees.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmediafileallowedextensions.description
data.value: File types (extensions) that can be uploaded to the media library (separated with a semicolon, without dot). Please note: If no value is specified, all types of files can be uploaded.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmediafilehiddenfolder.description
data.value: Name of the folder which is located in each media library subfolder. All file previews and image thumbnails of the files from the current subfolder are stored in its hidden folder. This folder is hidden both in administration UI and on the live site.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmediafilepreviewsuffix.description
data.value: Media file thumbnail suffix for identification of thumbnail file. Format of the thumbnail file name: &lt filename &gt _ &lt fileextension &gt&lt thumbnailsuffix &gt . &lt thumbnailextension &gt

data.name: settingskey.cmsmediaimagewatermark.description
data.value: If checked, the watermark is used for media files.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmedialibrariesfolder.description
data.value: Physical path to the folder where root folders of all media libraries should be stored. For example "~/Libraries", "c:/Libraries" or "\\servername\Libraries". If empty "~/[site name]/media" will be used.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmedialibrarymaxsubfolders.description
data.value: Maximum number of folders that will be displayed under unfolded folder in the folder tree view.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmediausepermanenturls.description
data.value: If set to true, URLs of the media library files will be generated as permanent links using getmediafile.aspx.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmembermanagementpath.description
data.value: Alias path of member management page, e.g. "/Members/{UserName}/Management", where {UserName} will be replaced by the user name.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmemberprofilepath.description
data.value: Alias path for member profile page, e.g. "/Members/{UserName}", where {UserName} will be replaced by the user name.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmembershipreminder.description
data.value: Number of days before membership expiration when notification is to be sent to the user.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmergecontactsforcustomers
data.value: Merge contacts for identical E-commerce customers

data.name: settingskey.cmsmergecontactsforcustomers.description
data.value: Automatic contact merging will occur whenever multiple contacts exists for e-commerce customer.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmergecontactsforsubscribers
data.value: Merge contacts for identical Newsletter subscribers

data.name: settingskey.cmsmergecontactsforsubscribers.description
data.value: Automatic contact merge will occur when multiple contacts exist for newsletter subscriber.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmergecontactsforuser.description
data.value: Automatic contact merging will occur whenever multiple contacts exist for single user.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmessagingemailfrom.description
data.value: Notification e-mail address of the email sender.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmetaimagewatermark.description
data.value: If checked, the watermark is used for object attachments.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmetaweblogdeleteattachments.description
data.value: Indicates whether the post attachments should be removed when not used anymore.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmetawebloggeneratesummary.description
data.value: Indicates whether the characters from blog post body should be copied as a blog post summary text. Number of characters is specified by 'Summary length' setting.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmetaweblogsummarylength.description
data.value: Number of characters copied by automatic summary to populate blog post summary.

data.name: settingskey.cmsminwatermarkimageheight.description
data.value: Minimum height of an image to be watermarked.

data.name: settingskey.cmsminwatermarkimagewidth.description
data.value: Minimum width of an image to be watermarked.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmonitorbouncedemails.description
data.value: Indicates if bounced e-mails should be monitored.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmoveviewstatetoend
data.value: Move ViewState to the end of the page

data.name: settingskey.cmsmoveviewstatetoend.description
data.value: If checked, the ViewState field is moved to the end of the page which results in more content being processed by the search engines.

data.name: settingskey.cmsmvtenabled.description
data.value: Indicates whether multivariate testing module is enabled

data.name: settingskey.cmsnewdocumentorder.description
data.value: Specifies the default order of new inserted document.

data.name: settingskey.cmsnewsletterunsubscriptionurl.description
data.value: Default URL where newsletter unsubscription page is placed. If not specified, '~/CMSPages/Unsubscribe.aspx' is used.

data.name: settingskey.CMSNewsletterUseExternalService
data.value: Use external service for dynamic newsletters

data.name: settingskey.CMSNewsletterUseExternalService.description
data.value: If enabled, the scheduled tasks that are created to ensure the mail-out of new dynamic newsletters will be set to be processed by the external scheduling Windows service by default. Please note that this does not change the settings of existing dynamic newsletter tasks.

data.name: settingskey.cmsnoreplyemailaddress.description
data.value: System will use this email address for sending various types of automated emails.

data.name: settingskey.cmsobjectversionhistorylength.description
data.value: Determines the maximum number of minor object versions (per object) saved in database. If 0, minor versions history length is not limited.

data.name: settingskey.cmsobjectversionhistorymajorversionslength.description
data.value: Determine maximal number of major object versions (per object) saved in database. If 0 major versions history length is not limited.

data.name: settingskey.cmsobjectversionhistorypromotetomajortimeinterval
data.value: Promote to major version if older than (hours)

data.name: settingskey.cmsobjectversionhistorypromotetomajortimeinterval.description
data.value: Determines the number of hours between modifications of an object needed to promote an object version to a major version. If 0, no promoting occurs automatically.

data.name: settingskey.cmsobjectversionhistoryuselastversioninterval
data.value: Save to last version if younger than (minutes)

data.name: settingskey.cmsobjectversionhistoryuselastversioninterval.description
data.value: Indicates if the last version should be used to store actual object data instead of creating a new version when an object is edited within the specified time interval. If 0, a new version is always created.

data.name: settingskey.cmsopenidroles.description
data.value: Registred OpenID users will be assigned to these roles. Separated by (;)

data.name: settingskey.cmsoptinapprovalurl
